We use a deep neural network with fully connected dense layers as shown in Fig. 1. Our deep learning approach is built upon the open source keras library in python99. Our optimized DNN uses 8 fully connected dense layers with 400 neurons per layer, and both MLPs are 4 layers of 50 neurons each. Optimization of the hyperparameters is performed with the built-in hyperband optimization method100. We also utilize manual cross-fold validation for limited hyperparameter optimization. For training, we utilize a MSE loss function and validate/evaluate using an MAE score based on Eqs. (1, 2) respectively, where Yi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
