While we can choose to define thermal optimization equation for specific applications such as radiative cooling or heating, high temperature cooling, etc., for this work we use a simple relation for easy comparison in the unseen material predictions. The cost function used in this work neglects solar absorption and focuses only on maximizing thermal emission. We define the objective function with the heat transfer balance,5Ccooling=Pmax,rad-Prad+Pabs+PtransPmax,rad+Psolar\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
